From 05f281be90c90c6599af61fa26e6ea1618957e2d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: TC8 Mainline Port <tc8@polycom-re.local>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 19:53:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] net: dsa: realtek: add RTL8363NB-VB switch support
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The Polycom TC8 uses a Realtek RTL8363NB-VB integrated 3-port gigabit
switch on its FEC1 RGMII link.  The chip identifies as 0x6511 and is
electrically a sibling of the RTL8365MB-VC supported by rtl8365mb.c,
but it requires a substantially different bring-up sequence:

  1. A 63-entry stock SoC-side register replay extracted from the
     Polycom kernel.  Without this the chip enumerates but no PHY
     ever links up.
  2. An 8051 microcode loader (1507 bytes) that programs the on-die
     management CPU.  The blob is embedded as a static const array
     for now; when integrating into a wider tree it should move to
     /lib/firmware/rtl8363nbvb-8051.bin and request_firmware().
  3. A 210-entry PHY OCP patch table replaying the per-PHY analog
     trims that the stock vendor driver applies.
  4. NBVB-specific RGMII tweaks on port 6 (uplink).
  5. A post-setup iso-mask reopen, because the chip drops some port
     enable bits during the firmware bring-up.

In addition:

  - drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek-mdio.c retries chip detect up to
    eight times with a 250 ms gap.  The chip is silent for several
    hundred milliseconds after u-boot hands off; a single attempt
    races on cold boot.
  - drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek.h bumps REALTEK_HW_STOP_DELAY
    and REALTEK_HW_START_DELAY to the values the stock vendor driver
    uses; the upstream defaults are too aggressive for this chip.

Compatible: realtek,rtl8365mb (existing) — board DT selects the
RTL8363NB-VB code path via the chip-id read at probe time.
---
 drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek-mdio.c |  13 +-
 drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek.h      |   4 +-
 drivers/net/dsa/realtek/rtl8365mb.c    | 772 ++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 3 files changed, 773 insertions(+), 16 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek-mdio.c b/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek-mdio.c
index 292e6d087..2e7b40b98 100644
--- a/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek-mdio.c
+++ b/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek-mdio.c
@@ -212,9 +212,18 @@ static int realtek_mdio_probe(struct mdio_device *mdiodev)
 		dev_dbg(dev, "deasserted RESET\n");
 	}
 
-	ret = priv->ops->detect(priv);
+	/* TC8: chip is sometimes silent after u-boot hand-off; retry */
+	{
+		int tries;
+		for (tries = 0; tries < 8; tries++) {
+			ret = priv->ops->detect(priv);
+			if (!ret) break;
+			dev_info(dev, "detect retry %d, sleeping 250ms\n", tries);
+			msleep(250);
+		}
+	}
 	if (ret) {
-		dev_err(dev, "unable to detect switch\n");
+		dev_err(dev, "unable to detect switch after retries\n");
 		return ret;
 	}
 
diff --git a/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek.h b/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek.h
index 4fa7c6ba8..7c7080e42 100644
--- a/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek.h
+++ b/drivers/net/dsa/realtek/realtek.h
